{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ViewThatFits"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/viewthatfits\/togglestyle(_:)"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ViewThatFits\/toggleStyle(_:)"},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"toggleStyle"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"S"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"style"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP0aB2UIE11toggleStyleyQrqd__AD06ToggleG0Rd__lFQO1Sqd__mfp","text":"S"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","text":"View"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"where"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"S"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:11OpenSwiftUI11ToggleStyleP","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ToggleStyle","text":"ToggleStyle"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The toggle style to set. Use one of the built-in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values, like "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ToggleStyle\/switch","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ToggleStyle\/button"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or a custom style that you define by creating a type that conforms"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ToggleStyle","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol."}]}],"name":"style"}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Return Value","level":2,"anchor":"return-value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A view that uses the specified toggle style for itself"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and its child views."}]}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use this modifier on a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Toggle","isActive":true},{"text":" instance to set a style that defines","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the control’s appearance and behavior. For example, you can choose","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ToggleStyle\/switch","isActive":true},{"text":" style:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["Toggle(\"Vibrate on Ring\", isOn: $vibrateOnRing)","    .toggleStyle(.switch)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Built-in styles typically have a similar appearance across platforms,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tailored to the platform’s overall style:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Platform"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Appearance","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS, iPadOS","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"macOS","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"header":"row"},{"text":"Styling toggles in a hierarchy","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Styling-toggles-in-a-hierarchy"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can set a style for all toggle instances within a view hierarchy"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"by applying the style modifier to a container view. For example, you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can apply the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ToggleStyle\/button"},{"type":"text","text":" style to an "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/HStack","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["HStack {","    Toggle(isOn: $isFlagged) {","        Label(\"Flag\", systemImage: \"flag.fill\")","    }","    Toggle(isOn: $isMuted) {","        Label(\"Mute\", systemImage: \"speaker.slash.fill\")","    }","}",".toggleStyle(.button)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example above has the following appearance when "},{"code":"isFlagged","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"isMuted","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Platform","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Appearance","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS, iPadOS","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"macOS","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]]],"header":"row"},{"text":"Automatic styling","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Automatic-styling"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you don’t set a style, OpenSwiftUI assumes a value of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"ToggleStyle\/automatic","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", which corresponds to a context-specific"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"default. Specify the automatic style explicitly to override a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"container’s style and revert to the default:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["HStack {","    Toggle(isOn: $isShuffling) {","        Label(\"Shuffle\", systemImage: \"shuffle\")","    }","    Toggle(isOn: $isRepeating) {","        Label(\"Repeat\", systemImage: \"repeat\")","    }","","    Divider()","","    Toggle(\"Enhance Sound\", isOn: $isEnhanced)","        .toggleStyle(.automatic) \/\/ Revert to the default style.","}",".toggleStyle(.button) \/\/ Use button style for toggles in the stack.",".labelStyle(.iconOnly) \/\/ Omit the title from any labels."],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The style that OpenSwiftUI uses as the default depends on both the platform"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and the context. In macOS, the default in most contexts is a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ToggleStyle\/checkbox"},{"type":"text","text":", while in iOS, the default toggle style is a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ToggleStyle\/switch","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Platform"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Appearance"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS, iPadOS","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"macOS","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"header":"row"},{"name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Like toggle style does for toggles, the "},{"code":"View\/labelStyle(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modifier sets the style for "},{"code":"Label","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instances in the hierarchy. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"example above demostrates the compact "},{"code":"LabelStyle\/iconOnly","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" style,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which is useful for button toggles in space-constrained contexts."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Always include a descriptive title for better accessibility."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","style":"note"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For more information about how OpenSwiftUI chooses a default toggle style,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"see the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ToggleStyle\/automatic"},{"type":"text","text":" style."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI","relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"]}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"toggleStyle"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP0aB2UIE11toggleStyleyQrqd__AD06ToggleG0Rd__lFQO1Sqd__mfp","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"S"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"View"}],"remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/bl